(42, 2, 30, 1, 49, 18, 18, 'thy salvation', 'Connection of Salvation in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation. Luke 2:30 expresses the fulfillment of seeing salvation, while Genesis 49:18 reflects a longing for it.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 30, 23, 52, 10, 10, 'thy salvation', 'Connection of Salvation in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation being revealed to all nations. Luke 2:30 speaks of seeing salvation, while Isaiah 52:10 declares that all the ends of the earth shall see the salvation of our God.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 30, 42, 2, 10, 11, 'thy salvation', 'Connection of Salvation and Saviour', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation, with the angel proclaiming the birth of a Saviour, which directly relates to Simeon''s acknowledgment of having seen God''s salvation. This connection highlights the fulfillment of the promise of salvation through Christ''s birth.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 30, 42, 3, 6, 6, 'thy salvation', 'Connection of Salvation in Luke', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of salvation. The SOURCE verse expresses personal recognition of salvation, while the TARGET passage proclaims that all flesh will see it.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 30, 10, 23, 1, 5, 'thy salvation', 'Connection of Salvation Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of salvation. In Luke, Simeon recognizes Jesus as salvation, while David speaks of God''s covenant as his salvation.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 30, 44, 4, 10, 12, 'thy salvation', 'Connection of Salvation in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation. In Luke, salvation is seen through the eyes of Simeon, while in Acts, salvation is explicitly linked to the name of Jesus Christ.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 31, 23, 42, 1, 4, 'prepared before the face of all people', 'Servant and Judgment Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of a servant bringing forth judgment. Luke 2:31 speaks of God''s preparation for all people, while Isaiah 42:1-4 describes the servant who will bring judgment to the Gentiles. This connection highlights the universal scope of God''s plan.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 31, 23, 62, 1, 2, 'before the face of all people', 'Connection of Salvation and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation being revealed to all people. Luke speaks of God''s preparation for all nations, while Isaiah highlights the visibility of righteousness to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 31, 19, 98, 2, 3, 'before the face of all people', 'Connection of Salvation and Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the public revelation of God''s salvation. Luke highlights that it is prepared ''before the face of all people,'' while Psalms declares that God''s salvation has been shown ''in the sight of the heathen.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 31, 19, 96, 10, 13, 'prepared before the face of all people', 'Divine Judgment and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s preparation and judgment. Both passages emphasize God''s authority and righteousness in judging the people and the world.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 31, 19, 97, 6, 8, 'prepared before the face of all people', 'Divine Preparation and Glory', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s preparation and revelation to all people. Both passages emphasize the visibility of God''s glory and righteousness before humanity.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 31, 23, 45, 21, 25, 'all people', 'Salvation for All People', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s universal salvation. Both passages emphasize that God has prepared salvation for all people, as seen in Luke''s reference to ''all people'' and Isaiah''s call to ''all the ends of the earth.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 32, 23, 60, 1, 3, 'light to lighten the Gentiles', 'Light and Glory Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light and glory, with Luke referencing a light for the Gentiles and Isaiah proclaiming that the glory of the Lord will be seen. The mention of Gentiles coming to the light in Isaiah parallels Luke''s declaration of light for the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 32, 23, 49, 6, 6, 'a light to lighten the Gentiles', 'Light to the Gentiles Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being a light to the Gentiles, indicating a broader mission beyond Israel. This connection highlights the role of salvation extending to all nations.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 32, 44, 26, 23, 23, 'a light to lighten the Gentiles', 'Light to Gentiles Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Christ as a light for the Gentiles. Luke 2:32 presents this idea in the context of Jesus'' birth, while Acts 26:23 connects it to His resurrection and mission.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 32, 44, 13, 47, 48, 'a light to lighten the Gentiles', 'Light to the Gentiles', 'Both passages emphasize the role of being a light to the Gentiles, highlighting the mission to bring salvation to all nations. The connection illustrates the continuity of this theme from Jesus'' early recognition to its fulfillment in the apostles'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 32, 66, 21, 23, 23, 'the glory of thy people Israel', 'Light and Glory Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light and glory. Luke 2:32 speaks of a light for the Gentiles and the glory of Israel, while Revelation 21:23 describes the glory of God as the source of light in the city.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 32, 38, 2, 5, 5, 'the glory of thy people Israel', 'Connection of Glory and Light', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of glory, with Luke referring to the glory of Israel and Zechariah stating that the Lord will be the glory in her midst. Additionally, the idea of divine presence and protection in Zechariah complements the light motif in Luke, suggesting a broader theme of God''s revelation to both Israel and the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 32, 40, 4, 16, 16, 'light to lighten the Gentiles', 'Light and Darkness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of light illuminating darkness. Luke 2:32 speaks of a light for the Gentiles, while Matthew 4:16 describes people in darkness seeing great light.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 33, 23, 8, 18, 18, 'marvelled at those things', 'Signs and Wonders Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of marveling at divine signs. Both passages emphasize the significance of children as signs and wonders from God.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 33, 42, 1, 65, 66, 'marvelled at those things', 'Marvel and Wonder at Birth', 'This connection highlights the sense of wonder surrounding the births of both Jesus and John the Baptist. Both passages emphasize the reactions of those who hear about these miraculous events, leading to questions about the significance of these children.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 33, 42, 2, 48, 48, 'marvelled at those things', 'Parental Amazement and Concern', 'Both passages emphasize the amazement of Mary and Joseph. In the first, they marvel at the words spoken about Jesus, and in the second, they express their astonishment at finding him after searching. This connection highlights the emotional responses of his parents to Jesus''s actions.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 34, 46, 1, 23, 23, 'for the fall and rising again', 'Connection of Stumbling and Rising', 'This connection highlights the theme of Christ as a polarizing figure. Both passages emphasize the ''fall'' and ''rising again'' of many, illustrating how Jesus is perceived differently by various groups.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 34, 60, 2, 7, 8, 'fall and rising again', 'Connection of Stumbling and Rising', 'Both passages emphasize the duality of Jesus'' role, highlighting how he is set for the ''fall and rising again'' of many, while also being a ''stone of stumbling'' for the disobedient. This connection illustrates the contrasting responses to Jesus'' presence and message.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 34, 23, 8, 14, 15, 'for the fall and rising again', 'Connection of Stumbling and Rising', 'Both passages emphasize the dual nature of the child as a cause for both rising and falling among Israel. Simeon''s declaration in Luke reflects the prophetic warning in Isaiah about the child being a stone of stumbling.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 34, 40, 21, 44, 44, 'fall and rising again of many', 'Connection of Fall and Rising', 'This connection highlights the themes of falling and rising associated with Jesus. Both passages emphasize the consequences of one''s response to Him, whether leading to brokenness or destruction.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 34, 44, 9, 1, 20, 'fall and rising again of many in Israel', 'Fall and Rising Again', 'Both passages emphasize the transformative journey of individuals in relation to Jesus. Simeon''s prophecy about the ''fall and rising again'' connects to Saul''s dramatic conversion, illustrating the theme of spiritual awakening and the reversal of one''s path.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 34, 28, 14, 9, 9, 'fall and rising again of many', 'Fall and Rising Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of falling and rising, as Simeon speaks of the child being set for the ''fall and rising again of many in Israel,'' while Hosea notes that ''the just shall walk in them: but the transgressors shall fall therein.'' Both passages emphasize the consequences of one''s actions in relation to God''s ways.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 34, 47, 2, 15, 16, 'fall and rising again', 'Connection of Life and Death', 'Both passages emphasize the duality of responses to Christ, highlighting the ''fall and rising again'' in Luke and the ''savour of death unto death'' and ''savour of life unto life'' in Corinthians. This connection illustrates the contrasting outcomes of faith and rejection.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 2, 35, 5, 8, 2, 2, 'thoughts of many hearts may be revealed', 'Revealing Hearts and Testing Faith', 'This connection highlights the theme of revealing what is in the heart. Both passages emphasize the importance of understanding inner thoughts and intentions, whether through trials in the wilderness or through personal suffering.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
